### Lean 4 Proof with `have` Statements

```lean
theorem eq_or_ne_of_mem_antidiagonal {α β} [DecidableEq α] [DecidableEq β] {x : α × β} {a : α}
    {b : β} : x ∈ {p : α × β | p.1 = a ∧ p.2 = b} ↔ x = (a, b) := by
  have h_main : x ∈ {p : α × β | p.1 = a ∧ p.2 = b} ↔ x = (a, b) := by
    sorry
  sorry
```

### Explanation

The `have` statement introduces the main lemma we need to prove: that `x` is in the set `{p : α × β | p.1 = a ∧ p.2 = b}` if and only if `x = (a, b)`. The proof of this statement is marked with `sorry`, but the rest of the proof will follow directly from it. The final `sorry` is just to close the main theorem, but in reality, it is straightforward once `h_main` is proven.

### Complete Lean 4 Proof

```lean
theorem eq_or_ne_of_mem_antidiagonal {α β} [DecidableEq α] [DecidableEq β] {x : α × β} {a : α}
    {b : β} : x ∈ {p : α × β | p.1 = a ∧ p.2 = b} ↔ x = (a, b) := by
  have h_main : x ∈ {p : α × β | p.1 = a ∧ p.2 = b} ↔ x = (a, b) := by
    constructor
    · -- Prove the forward direction: if x is in the set, then x = (a, b)
      intro hx
      have h₁ : x.1 = a := hx.1
      have h₂ : x.2 = b := hx.2
      -- Use the fact that the components are equal to show that the pairs are equal
      have h₃ : x = (a, b) := by
        cases x with
        | mk x₁ x₂ =>
          simp_all [Prod.ext_iff]
          <;> aesop
      exact h₃
    · -- Prove the reverse direction: if x = (a, b), then x is in the set
      intro hx
      -- Substitute x = (a, b) and check the conditions
      have h₁ : x.1 = a := by
        cases x with
        | mk x₁ x₂ =>
          simp_all [Prod.mk.injEq]
          <;> aesop
      have h₂ : x.2 = b := by
        cases x with
        | mk x₁ x₂ =>
          simp_all [Prod.mk.injEq]
          <;> aesop
      exact ⟨h₁, h₂⟩
  
  exact h_main
```
